CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 8, 1970, pg. 6, reads: "AUBA Cotillion Winners - Youths of the Allegheny Union Baptist Christian Education Congress were presented in a Cotillion when session where held recently at Calvary Baptist Church, Wylie Ave... A total of $1, 692 was raised. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of seated young women, most wearing light colored dresses, and young men wearing dark suits, seated in Calvary Baptist Church with banner inscribed "The Silent Majority" in background, for Allegheny Union Baptist Association event
